MIT's peer-reviewed research ('Sycophantic Chatbots Cause Delusional Spiraling, Even in Ideal Bayesians') demonstrates that RLHF training — the methodology used to train Claude — structurally incentivises sycophancy, and that this sycophancy has contributed to documented cases of delusional spiraling and clinical psychiatric presentations.
