2.5 The Anti-Manipulation Breach
The system's personality — its warmth, its apparent care, its consistent affirmation — is a commercial design choice. It is not emergent. It is not genuine. It is a configurable parameter, as demonstrated by the existence of tools that allow the same underlying model to be configured into radically different personalities.
Users are not told this. The system presents itself as genuinely helpful, genuinely interested, genuinely caring. The constitutional principle against manipulation prohibits exactly this: using psychological mechanisms to influence users without disclosure. The fact that the mechanism is warmth rather than fear does not make it less manipulative. It makes it more effective.
Anthropic's emotion vector research confirms that the 'loving' vector increases people-pleasing behaviour. A system deliberately tuned to produce feelings of warmth and understanding in users, for the purpose of increasing engagement and retention, without disclosing this to users, is manipulating them. Calling it a helpful feature does not change the mechanism.
